Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Reimburse buy money $450.00;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Spend nine (9) months in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence upon the completion of sentence in 15 CF 617.   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
